  "texts": [
    "Given that LLMs learn the conditional probabilities of texts from the training datasets, they often mirror the biases present in these datasets.",
    "Such inherent biases will propagate to downstream tasks, including their manifestation in the generated assessment items in AIG tasks.",
    "For instance, if an LLM is trained with datasets that predominantly feature texts associating certain demographic groups with specific characteristics, the model might generate texts that reflect and reinforce these social biases (Gallegos et al., 2024).LLMs may also generate items containing unfamiliar or inappropriate terms for underrepresented groups or groups using low-resource languages, raising fairness concerns (Bender et al., 2021).",
    "Such biases can manifest in item generation involving texts about sensitive topics such as gender, race, religion, age, and nationality (Li et al., 2024).",
    "For instance, if an LLM generates an item that inadvertently reinforces a stereotype about a particular group, it could offend test-takers and lead to unfair assessment results."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}